{"id":"math/9809144","submitter":"Maxim Braverman","authors":"Maxim Braverman","title":"Vanishing theorems on covering manifolds","comments":"LaTeX 2e; 25 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DG math.AG math.RT","license":null,"abstract":"  Let $M$ be an oriented even-dimensional Riemannian manifold on which a\ndiscrete group $\\Gamma$ of orientation-preserving isometries acts freely, so\nthat the quotient $X=M/\\Gamma$ is compact. We prove a vanishing theorem for a\nhalf-kernel of a $\\Gamma$-invariant Dirac operator on a $\\Gamma$-equivariant\nClifford module over $M$, twisted by a sufficiently large power of a\n$\\Gamma$-equivariant line bundle, whose curvature is non-degenerate at any\npoint of $M$. This generalizes our previous vanishing theorems for Dirac\noperators on a compact manifold.\n  In particular, if $M$ is an almost complex manifold we prove a vanishing\ntheorem for the half-kernel of a $\\spin^c$ Dirac operator, twisted by a line\nbundle with curvature of a mixed sign. In this case we also relax the\nassumption of non-degeneracy of the curvature. When $M$ is a complex manifold\nour results imply analogues of Kodaira and Andreotti-Grauert vanishing theorems\nfor covering manifolds.\n  As another application, we show that semiclassically the $\\spin^c$\nquantization of an almost complex covering manifold gives an \"honest\" Hilbert\nspace. This generalizes a result of Borthwick and Uribe, who considered\nquantization of compact manifolds.\n  Application of our results to homogeneous manifolds of a real semisimple Lie\ngroup leads to new proofs of Griffiths-Schmidt and Atiyah-Schmidt vanishing\ntheorems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Sep 1998 17:01:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
